  "text": "where H is a function to assess the quality of the 2r multiobjective solutions, and H can be any performance indicator, e.g., the hypervolume (HV) indicator [CITATION_1] as adopted in this paper. By using such a reformulation scheme, the scale of the original problem can be substantially reduced. For example, an LSMOP with 1000 decision variables can be reformulated into an SOP with only ten decision variables as in our experiments.",
